<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<title>Topic 4: URL-based access control can be circumvented</title>
		<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
		<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js" integrity="sha256-/JqT3SQfawRcv/BIHPThkBvs0OEvtFFmqPF/lYI/Cxo=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
		<script src="/js/home.main.js"></script>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/global.css" />
	</head>
	<body class="flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen px-4 text-zinc-100">
		<div class="max-w-3xl text-center space-y-6">
			<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100">Topic 4: URL-based access control can be circumvented</h1>
			<p class="text-zinc-300 text-lg">This website has an unauthenticated admin panel at <span class="font-bold text-zinc-100">/admin</span>, but a front-end system has been configured to block external access to that path. However, the back-end application is built on a framework that supports the <span class="font-bold text-zinc-100">X-Original-URL</span> header.</p>
			<p class="text-zinc text-lg font-bold"><span class="underline">Objective:</span> access the admin panel and delete the user carlos.</p>
			<p class="text-zinc text-lg font-bold">
				<% if(isCarlosDeleted){ %>
				<span class="text-green-500">You have completed the objective!</span>
				<% } else { %>
				<span class="text-red-500">You have not completed the objective yet.</span>
				<% } %>
			</p>
			<a href="<%= user ? '/profile' : '/login' %>" class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-zinc-700 hover:bg-zinc-600 rounded-lg text-white font-medium transition-colors"> <% if(user){ %> Go to <%= user.username %>'s Profile → <% } else{ %> Go to Login Page → <% } %> </a>
			<% if(user){ %>
			<button id="logout-button" class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-zinc-700 hover:bg-zinc-600 rounded-lg text-white font-medium transition-colors">Logout</button>
			<% } %>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
